    {
      "id": "document-authoring-contract-overview",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Scope",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": -80,
        "y": -160
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Scope\n\nA Twilite document graph is not just a markdown note. It is a structured authored artifact that composes document meaning from explicit document-publishing nodes such as `section`, `reference`, `figure`, `embed`, `annotation`, and `document-summary`.\n\nThis contract governs how those nodes are authored, ordered, surfaced, and validated.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "markdown"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "document-authoring-contract-rules",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Authoring Rules",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 500,
        "y": -160
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Authoring Rules\n\n1. Use document-publishing node classes for document structure instead of flattening the document into one giant markdown node.\n2. Keep the graph declaration and the document view surface aligned; the document view should be an explicit composed surface, not an accidental side effect.\n3. Preserve authored order intentionally. If the document surface depends on ordered parts, that order belongs in a real contract and should be validated.\n4. Use `document-summary` for outward summary surfaces and `document-view` for the full composed reading surface.\n5. Treat figures, embeds, references, and annotations as typed authored parts, not loose presentation extras.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "markdown"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "document-authoring-contract-anti-patterns",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Anti-Patterns",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 1040,
        "y": 220
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Anti-Patterns\n\n- A document graph that stores the whole artifact as one markdown blob while still pretending to be structured document authoring\n- A document view that has no explicit source ordering or no declared source nodes\n- A summary surface that is missing or not aligned with the document identity\n- Document authoring guidance that teaches the nodeset, template, and surface contract separately with no connecting law",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "markdown"
      }
    },
